# SciOlympics

SciOly practice platform: Next.js App Router + Supabase + Vercel. Link-based resource repo now; async ghost-race quizzes later (solo run vs recorded ghost — no realtime matchmaking).

## In scope (default)
- **L0**: `events`, `users` (Supabase Auth + profile FK, division B/C)
- **L1**: `resources` (title, url, description, event FK) — link-only, no uploads

## Out of scope (don't build unless asked)
- **L3**: `questions`, `runs`, `answers`
- **L4**: `matches`, `recordings`, ratings

## Commands
`npm run dev` · `npm run build` · `npm run lint`

## Repo map
- `src/app/` — pages, layouts, API routes
- `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` — browser client
- `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` — server/RSC client (cookies)
- `.env.local` from `.env.local.example` — never commit

## Schema rules
- `events.practice_type`: `quiz | hybrid | build` (quiz vs repo-only)
- Events in DB, not hardcoded (slate rotates yearly)
- On signup: create `users` profile row linked to `auth.users`
- **Future grading**: server-side only; correct answers never to client

## Build discipline
- Minimal diffs; reuse existing patterns
- Next.js APIs may differ from training data — check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` when unsure
- Full narrative spec: `CLAUDE.md`
